📌 What is Amazon Route 53 Domain Registration?
          Route 53 allows you to register and manage domain names directly from AWS. When you register a domain, 
          AWS automatically creates a Hosted Zone for it 
          — which holds your DNS records. Domain registration is a paid service and is not covered by AWS Free Tier.
🌐 Part 1 — Register a Domain in Route 53:

          Step 1 — Navigate to Route 53:
                    Go to AWS Console → Search "Route 53" → Click "Route 53"
                    On the Route 53 homepage → Click "Get started"
                    ⚠️ Note: Route 53 domain registration is NOT free.
                    Domain pricing varies by TLD (e.g. .com starts at ~$13/year). You will be charged immediately upon registration.
          Step 2 — Select Registration Option:
                    You will see two options:
                    Register a domain
                    Create a hosted zone
                    Select → "Register a domain" ✅
                    Click "Get started"
          Step 3 — Search for Your Domain:
                    In the domain search box → Type:
                    needtoknowEc2.com
                    Click "Search" ✅
                    You will see one of two results:
                    Result	Meaning
                    Available	Domain is free to register — proceed
                    Unavailable	Already taken — try a different name or TLD
                    💡 If needtoknowEc2.com is available → Click "Add to cart" → Click "Proceed to checkout"
          Step 4 — Choose Registration Duration:
                    Setting	                    Value
                    Registration Duration	1 year (default)
                    Auto-Renew	          Enable or disable as preferred
                    Click "Next" ✅
          Step 5 — Enter Contact / Address Details:
                    Fill in the registrant contact information:
                    Field	          Value
                    Contact Type	Person
                    First Name	Your first name
                    Last Name	Your last name
                    Organization	Optional
                    Email Address	Your valid email
                    Phone Number	Your phone with country code
                    Address Line 1	Your street address
                    City	Your city
                    State / Province	Your state
                    ZIP / Postal Code	Your postal code
                    Country	Your country
          ⚠️ Important: Enter accurate and valid contact details. ICANN (the global domain authority) requires real registrant information. Fake details can result in domain suspension.
                    Check the box → "I have read and agree to the AWS Domain Name Registration Agreement" ✅
                    Click "Submit" ✅
          Step 6 — Verify Your Email:
                    AWS will send a verification email to the address you provided
                    Open the email → Click "Verify" ✅
                    ⚠️ If you do not verify within 15 days — your domain will be suspended by ICANN.
          Step 7 — Wait for Registration to Complete:
                    Registration typically takes a few minutes up to 24 hours
                    You will receive a confirmation email from AWS once complete
                    Status in Route 53 will change from Pending → Active ✅
